    "body": "Currently, with other environments, there is no way to use multiple compiler versions in the same project -- correct?  So this is an issue that no one struggles with at the moment.\r\n\r\nBy introducing approach #1 you would make it invisible to the end-user but you're solving a problem that doesn't yet cause anyone pain.\r\n\r\nGiven that using contracts compiled with diff versions is more of an \"advanced user\" approach -- you should know the benefits and detriments to doing this rather than doing it blindly -- I'd tend towards the second approach. Especially if it is a lot less work to implement.  Then if the feature is used, #1 could be the next phase.",
